        - <span>SPORT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>MADRID • Spain’s World Cup-win­ning goal­keeper Iker Casil­las an­nounced his re­tire­ment yes­ter­day, af­ter be­ing side­lined for over a year fol­low­ing a heart at­tack.</p>
    <p>He said on Twit­ter that it was “both one of the most im­por­tant and most dif­fi­cult days of my sport­ing life”. The 39-year-old, who joined Porto in 2015, won five La Liga and three Cham­pi­ons League ti­tles at Real Madrid. He played over 700 games for the Span­ish gi­ants.</p>


